======================================================================
SECTION 2: DISTANCE FROM SPECTRAL CENTER (y_k^2 = p/4)
======================================================================

    The "spectral center" is y_k^2 = p/4 for all k = 1,...,(p-1)/2.
    This gives |lambda_k|^2 = (p+1)/4 (the Paley value).
    Distance = sqrt(sum (y_k^2 - p/4)^2) = sqrt(var * m) where m = (p-1)/2.

    For p=3 mod 4: Paley achieves center (distance = 0).
    For p=1 mod 4: center not achievable. What's the distance pattern?


--- p = 7 ---
  Center: y_k^2 = 1.7500 for all k  (Paley value)
           H dist_from_center     Sum_y4 type           
  -------------------------------------------------------
         189           0.0000     9.1875                
         175           3.7417    23.1875 CYCLIC INT     

  Correlation(H, dist_from_center) = -1.0000
  => NEGATIVE: closer to center (flatter) = more H. PALEY WINS.

